<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-AF87EEBC-46C6-48A6-BEEA-0CCAFF5B836B" version="2" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-AF87EEBC-46C6-48A6-BEEA-0CCAFF5B836B" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Light/dark lines every swath after 1 meter after leading edge</title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-50B00AD6-0A38-41AB-B3CF-DCE2951AFA8A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "/><table id="GUID-53E5F599-B620-44AD-919D-C7253ABD770C" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Schematic overview 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Real example 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-C071F717-0A0E-4659-BBFE-B3616B116397" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C4D2E2C8-D872-419A-BD9C-9288B54307B5-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C4D2E2C8-D872-419A-BD9C-9288B54307B5-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-3A69205D-9030-4341-BEDE-45D879506957" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-CFCF89B6-8554-41D7-BC30-6A85EB0561DB-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-CFCF89B6-8554-41D7-BC30-6A85EB0561DB-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-EC1EAE23-40EC-4B10-A2C9-83873F76DC70" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Collect</title><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Symptoms</b> 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Thin dark of white lines in carriage direction which are visible in every swath.
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Lines appear in all colors simultaneously. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Only 1 line per mediastep/swath.
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The distance between the lines equal and is depended of the printmode.
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Lines are present during the whole print (also after 1 meter after leading edge).
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Appearance can be very similar to "<xref keyref="PQ_25" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-7D1AA9F8-C042-4F34-A6C0-89D7688B29C4.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text White/light lines in 1 primary color and its mixed colors?>White/light lines in 1 primary color and its mixed colors</xref>" 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Functional logging (if available)</b>
</p><p class="- topic/p ">
</p><p class="- topic/p "><i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Media step Accuracy</i>
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Light and/or dark lines might be visible in the print in case the deviation on the markers is larger than approx. 30 µm. (See picture below). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This means the orange and/or blue line are outside the green area.
</p><fig id="GUID-8DFDD2DA-74DB-464B-BD29-BB82147CC160" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-07BD16CF-C7B0-410A-B44B-8B2AE61D1FB6-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-07BD16CF-C7B0-410A-B44B-8B2AE61D1FB6-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">However this a second cause (Media step correction factor) which shows is no deviation in media step errors.
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ADAM-triggers</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">No ADAM triggers are available 
</p></section><section id="GUID-DDCC1BB0-B402-4010-9156-67DB737F3DE5" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Analyze/Repair</title><fig id="GUID-88DD830A-76A0-4C6E-8D83-1DC08764321D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-717D7F95-7445-459A-8F30-E4BE9C5AC20F-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-717D7F95-7445-459A-8F30-E4BE9C5AC20F-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-BB9BDDD1-E29C-42C5-BF10-2854E3AE4223" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Steps explanation</title><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-D963269B-E108-446A-A212-4581FEAA8740" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="4" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="30*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Type 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">To do 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check whether media step correction is set to 0
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Set media step correction factor to 0
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check whether the media is calibrated 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">In case the media isn’t calibrated an exclamation sign is visible in the UI. 
</p><fig id="GUID-B6F1A101-0BC6-4D7E-8367-BC30CF9F4B3F" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-51A04FF7-0AFC-4927-984F-8E1D3D278823-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-51A04FF7-0AFC-4927-984F-8E1D3D278823-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Perform media calibration including the leading edge 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Cut media before calibration 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Perform maintenance 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Operating video : 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><xref href="http://localhost:20346/VIDEO10004EN.US/video06/index.html" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot usertext?>Clean the Platen</xref> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> 
<xref href="http://localhost:20346/VIDEO10004EN.US/video19/index.html" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot usertext?>Clean the Buffer Plate</xref> 
</p></li></ul></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Perform media calibration including the leading edge 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Cut media before calibration 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check if AAC markers are selected in the RIP-controller
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Enable markers : Use Normal, Enhanced or Robust markers
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Based on the type of engine the markers can be Yellow, Black or White.
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Run SDS 15-6-024 and verify the results 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">10
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Printer is working well. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">11
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check whether the X-tran rollers are broken
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">12 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Calibrate media via SDS (21-6-002) 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">13 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Replace X-tran rollers 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Calibrate media in SDS
</p></li></ol></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="15DISA001" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-D2422B11-B63C-4FEC-AA37-86683DEF45CA.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 15 How to remove the rollers of the Xtran pinch?>15 How to remove the rollers of the Xtran pinch</xref>
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-2513E5DF-C282-453D-9841-6E539DB0EB51" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Evaluate/Prevention</title></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p ">When media step errors occur a white line can appear when the step error is too large. In case of overlapping steps a dark line will appear. In contrast to printhead failure the distance between white lines is fixed and there is only 1 line per mediastep. The distance of the lines depends on the printmode. In high quality modes the distance is smaller than when speed modes are used.
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Under normal conditions the media step controller is able to correct the media step errors. A visible media step during the whole print (&gt;1 meter) indicates an offset in this algorithm. In most cases these kind of visibility is caused by a wrong setting in the media-profile (MediaStep Correction factor), however a malfunction in the xtran rollers or encoder can also cause media step errors during printing.
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-BDE42A10-0DAA-46D3-99F7-D18695E3843E.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Solutions</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
